# `codegen`

`Bake` orchestrates proto output plus per-integration generation from `schema` DTOs.

Templates live under `codegen/templates/` and are embedded with `go:embed`.

`integration.go` maps config keys to template paths, output filenames, post-process hooks, extra emitters, and finalizers.

`go_proto.go` and `js_proto.go` generate lightweight protobuf codecs for consumers; keep Go, JS, and C# client targets conceptually parallel.

`codegen/` imports config and template data from `schema`; it should not define YAML schema structs or reimplement schema loading.

When adding an integration, register it in `integration.go` and add its templates and any `GenerateExtra` or `Finalize` hooks here. Full clients (`go-client`, `js-client`, `csharp-client`) own generated managers/codecs; engine bridges (`phaser`, `unity`, `ebiten`) should stay thin and depend on the matching full client output.
